$ Oracle: Extended statistics
@ extended statistics

The focus of *extended statistics* is to calculate → development/databases/Oracle/optimizer/statistics for
  • sets of → development/databases/Oracle/objects/tables/columns[columns] with correlating values (for example `city` and `state`, or `age` and `income`, or `temperature` and `ice_cream_sales` etc.)
  • expressions

sa:

 `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/stats/api/stats/extended/create`

  The (undocumented) → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/init-parameters
    • `_optimizer_extended_cursor_sharing`
    • `_optimizer_extended_cursor_sharing_rel`
    • `_optimizer_extended_stats_usage_control`
    • `_optimizer_extend_jppd_view_types`
